{
  "text": "IL-1a engages IL-1R in the lung and drives expression of the neutrophil chemokine, keratinocytes (KC). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] We observed that KC was increased in the BALF of WT mice exposed to beryllium and was attenuated in beryllium-exposed IL-1RKO mice (Figure 2c ). Thus our data suggest that release of IL-1a is required for neutrophil recruitment to the lung through induction of KC.",
  "correct_citation": {
